cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.CC 

The paper discusses topics related to artificial intelligence (belief dynamics, knowledge bases, abduction), databases (updates, query answering, integrity checking), logic (Horn logic, stratified negation, disjunctive logic programming), and computational complexity (minimal model reasoning, hyper tableaux calculus). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CL, and cs.CC.
